You've entered a kitchen. The room seems oddly familiar, as though it were only superficially different from the other rooms in the building.

What's that over there? It looks like it's a fridge. The fridge contains a raw chicken leg, so there's that. You can make out a closed oven. You can make out a table. On the table you can see a cookbook and a knife. What's that over there? It looks like it's a counter. You see a raw purple potato on the counter. You hear a noise behind you and spin around, but you can't see anything other than a stove. The stove is conventional. The stove appears to be empty. It would have been so cool if there was stuff on the stove.

There is an open screen door leading south. There is an open plain door leading west. You don't like doors? Why not try going east, that entranceway is not blocked by one. You need an exit without a door? You should try going north.
